$ System.Data.Common.DbConnection (class)

Base class for various vendor's → development/databases[database] connection.

A class that derives from `S.D.C.DbConnection` is for example `Oracle.DataAccess.Client.OracleConnection`.

An important class in the → Microsoft/dot-net/ADO framework that uses the functionality of `DbConnection` is
→ Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Data/Common/DataAdapter[`System.Data.Common.DataAdapter`].

{ Transactions

  A → development/databases/SQL/transaction[transaction] can be started by calling `BeginTrasaction()`. This method returns a
  → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Data/Common/DbTransaction[`System.Data.Common.DbTransaction`] object (which in turn has methods such as `Commit()` and `Rollback()`.

}

sa:

  The `CreateConnection()` method of the → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Data/Common/DbProviderFactory[`System.Data.Common.DbProviderFactory` class].

  → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Data/Common/DbConnection/context-connections
